The paper deals with blind deconvolution, which is a problem in signal processing and image processing. The introduction of sparsity and spectral flatness priors suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of Information Theory (cs.IT), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision (cs.CV), Signal Processing (cs.SP), or Numerical Analysis (cs.NA). The focus on performance guarantees and RIP-like properties further supports these sub-categories.
